Package: Rmlx
Type: Package
Title: R Interface to Apple's MLX library for GPU-accelerated arrays
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("David", "Hugh-Jones", email = "david@hughjones.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Author: David Hugh-Jones [aut, cre]
Maintainer: David Hugh-Jones <david@hughjones.com>
Description: An R interface to Apple's MLX library, allowing array operations on 
    Apple Silicon GPUs and CPUs. Features include shared memory between the chips,
    CUDA support, lazy evaluation and automatic differentiation.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    Rcpp (>= 1.0.10),
    methods
LinkingTo:
    Rcpp
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    bench,
    dplyr,
    ggplot2
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Config/testthat/edition: 3
SystemRequirements: MLX (Apple Machine Learning eXchange) with C/C++ headers and library; macOS on Apple Silicon
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
URL: https://hughjonesd.github.io/Rmlx/
